MENG 4323 - Introduction to Industrial Robotics
An overview of industrial robots including manipulator arm selection
guidelines and the application of robots in manufacturing and assembly.
Principles of kinematics, dynamics and control of robotic manipulators.
Robotic sensors, end effectors and actuators. Coordinate frames and
homogeneous transformations. Robotic system integration, and path
planning. Industrial robot programming in a laboratory setting. Three
hours of lecture per week with integrated laboratory sessions.
Prerequisite: MENG 3309, MATH 3203 and MATH 3305.
